The paper focuses on visual road detection and recognition for autonomous driving applications, which falls under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses recent state-of-the-art machine learning techniques, which are commonly found in the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper briefly touches on the commercial implementations and recent research works pertaining to road detections, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it relates to the safety and security of autonomous driving systems.
